    tags: ["Holy Sepulchre", "Jerusalem", "knights", "Holy Land", "papal order"],
    oneLiner: "The Equestrian Order of the Holy Sepulchre of Jerusalem, a papal order of knighthood dedicated to supporting the Christian presence and institutions in the Holy Land.",
    body: "The Equestrian Order of the Holy Sepulchre of Jerusalem traces its origins to the era of the Crusades, when Godfrey of Bouillon organized a group of knights to guard the Church of the Holy Sepulchre in Jerusalem. Reorganized in the nineteenth century and placed under the direct protection of the Holy See, it is today a lay Catholic order of pontifical right, the only lay institution charged with providing for the needs of the Latin Patriarchate of Jerusalem. Members (knights and ladies) are invested by the Cardinal Grand Master in a solemn ceremony and commit to supporting the Christian communities of the Holy Land through prayer, pilgrimage, and financial assistance. The Order funds schools, hospitals, parishes, and seminaries throughout Israel, Palestine, Jordan, and Cyprus, helping to sustain the 'living stones'—the Christian faithful who maintain a continuous presence in the land where Jesus lived, died, and rose.",
