    body: "The Enthronement of the Sacred Heart is a devotional practice in which a family formally installs an image of the Sacred Heart in a prominent place in the home and consecrates the household to Christ's love and kingship. Promoted by Blessed Mateo Crawley-Boevey, SS.CC., in the early twentieth century with the encouragement of Pope St. Pius X, the practice involves a ceremony (ideally led by a priest) that includes prayers of consecration, the enthronement of the image, and a commitment to live out the devotion through daily family prayer, First Friday observance, and acts of reparation. The theology underlying the practice is that Christ desires to reign not only in churches but in every Christian home, transforming family life from within through the power of His Sacred Heart. The devotion has been credited with strengthening countless families, bringing about conversions, and fostering a spirit of reparation.",
    example: "A family gathers in their living room as the parish priest blesses and installs an image of the Sacred Heart above the mantle. Together they pray the Act of Consecration, pledging to make their home a place where Christ's love reigns. Each evening afterward, they gather before the image for family prayers.",
