    id: "mex-fatima-first-saturday-practice",
    term: "Fatima First Saturday Practice",
    category: "devotions",
    tags: ["First Saturday", "Fatima", "reparation", "Immaculate Heart", "Lucia"],
    oneLiner: "The devotion of Five First Saturdays requested by Our Lady of Fatima in 1925, involving Confession, Communion, Rosary, and fifteen minutes of meditation in reparation to the Immaculate Heart of Mary.",
    body: "On December 10, 1925, the Blessed Virgin Mary appeared to Sister Lucia dos Santos in Pontevedra, Spain, requesting a devotion of reparation on five consecutive First Saturdays. The requirements are: go to Confession (within eight days before or after), receive Holy Communion, pray five decades of the Rosary, and spend fifteen minutes meditating on the mysteries of the Rosary—all offered in a spirit of reparation for offenses against the Immaculate Heart of Mary. Our Lady specified five Saturdays to correspond to five types of offenses: blasphemies against the Immaculate Conception, against Mary's perpetual virginity, against her divine maternity, teaching children contempt for Mary, and direct outrages against her sacred images. The devotion carries the promise that Mary will assist at the hour of death with all the graces necessary for salvation. Pope Pius XII consecrated the world to the Immaculate Heart of Mary in 1942, partially fulfilling Fatima's broader requests.",
    example: "On the first Saturday of each month, a parish offers a special early Mass followed by a guided meditation on the Rosary mysteries. Parishioners track their five consecutive First Saturdays on cards distributed by the parish Fatima apostolate, combining personal devotion with communal practice.",
    whyItMatters: "The First Saturday devotion connects personal Marian piety to the great prophetic messages of Fatima, channeling the faithful's love for Our Lady into concrete acts of reparation with eternal significance.",
