    id: "mex-seven-sorrows-rosary-deeper",
    term: "Seven Sorrows Rosary in Depth",
    category: "devotions",
    tags: ["Seven Sorrows", "Mary", "rosary", "Servite", "compassion"],
    oneLiner: "A detailed exploration of the chaplet meditating on Mary's seven sorrows, its Servite origins, and the promises associated with its devout recitation.",
    body: "The Rosary of the Seven Sorrows (also called the Servite Rosary or Chaplet of the Seven Dolors) meditates on the seven principal sorrows of the Blessed Virgin Mary: the prophecy of Simeon, the flight into Egypt, the loss of the Child Jesus in the Temple, Mary meeting Jesus on the way to Calvary, the Crucifixion, the taking down from the Cross, and the burial of Jesus. Originating with the Servite Order (founded in 1233 specifically to meditate on Mary's sorrows), the chaplet consists of seven groups of seven Hail Marys, each preceded by meditation on one sorrow. Revelations attributed to St. Bridget of Sweden include promises for those who devoutly pray this chaplet: true repentance before death, protection in tribulations, and the imprinting of Christ's Passion in their memory. The devotion was given new impetus by reported apparitions of the Blessed Virgin in Kibeho, Rwanda (1981-1989), where Our Lady specifically requested that this rosary be prayed.",
    example: "In Kibeho, Rwanda, the Blessed Virgin appeared to visionary Alphonsine Mumureke and taught her the Seven Sorrows Rosary, urging its daily recitation. Years later, when genocide devastated Rwanda in 1994, survivors credited the devotion with sustaining their faith and hope during unimaginable suffering.",
    whyItMatters: "The Seven Sorrows Rosary invites Catholics to enter into Mary's compassion at the foot of the Cross, learning through her example how to unite personal suffering with the redemptive Passion of Christ.",
